which version of ACL are you using?
If you use ACL version 19.08 you need to specify it.
see: https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/master/tools/ci_build/build.py#L336
it defaults to ACL_1905
so you would need to use --use_acl=ACL_1908

Can you share the steps to reproduce memory leak with ACL?

import numpy as np
import cv2
import onnxruntime as rt
model_path = './models/onnx/version-RFB-320.onnx'
img_path = 'dh6.jpg'
orig_image = cv2.imread(img_path)
so = rt.SessionOptions()
sess = rt.InferenceSession(model_path, sess_options=so, providers=['ACLExecutionProvider'])
input_name = sess.get_inputs()[0].name
label = sess.get_outputs()[0].name
box = sess.get_outputs()[1].name

image = cv2.cvtColor(orig_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)
image = (cv2.resize(image, (320, 240)) - 127.0)/128

image = np.transpose(image, [2, 0, 1])
image = np.expand_dims(image, axis=0)
image = image.astype(np.float32)

for i in range(1000):
    t0=time.time()
    confidences, boxes = sess.run(None, {input_name: image})
    print(time.time()-t0)

I was watching the memory usage when the last four lines was running. The memory usage was going up linearly.
